<plot>Touch explores the sensuality of a couple through the use of various bodies of water recorded at Niagara Falls, the Atlantic Ocean at Acadia National Park, the Caribbean Sea, Lake Michigan and different streams, fountains and waterfalls. The power and beauty of water unites the couple, and the variety of the water symbolizes the intensity of a relationship. In addition, using water visuals as a replacement for the human body, Touch displays water as an essential element in our lives.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?614206</url></doc>
